Minute Entry for proceedings held before US Magistrate Judge Marcos E. Lopez: Initial Appearance as to Carlos E. Acosta (8) was held on 10/30/2013. Defendant was provided with a copy of the Indictment. Defendant was advised as to the charges and as to his rights. After reviewing the CJA-23 form filled by defendant, the Court deemed it appropriate to appoint counsel. The defendant was previously appointed CJA Atty Joseph Boucher in CR. 12-895 (JAF). The Court found that in the interest of judicial economy and efficiency, Atty Joseph Boucher shall be directly appointed to represent the defendant in this matter. As to detention, defendant shall remain temporarily detained pending further proceedings. Arraignment/Bail Hearing is set for 11/12/2013 at 9:15 AM in Courtroom 10 before US Magistrate Judge Marcos E. Lopez. Minute Entry for proceedings held before US Magistrate Judge Camille L. Velez- Rive:Arraignment/Detention as to Jose E. Gonzalez-Santiago (3) Count 1,2 held on 10/30/2013. Present were AUSA Carlos Cardona and Mr. Rafael Anglada. Dft was present and under custody. Defendant was found competent at this time to understand the proceedings. He/She waived the reading of the Indictment and entered a plea of not guilty  as to all counts. The parties will have 7 days for discovery and 14 days thereafter to file any motions. Case is referred to Judge Fuste for scheduling. As to bail, Mr. Anglada stated that they had nothing to offer at this time, but reserved the right to reopen hearing. The Court ordered defendant detained without bail. Order to issue. (Court Reporter - FTR.)Hearing set for 09:00.Hearing held at 10:40.Hearing ended at 10:44. Interpreter - Sonia Crescioni. (yr) (Entered: 11/06/2013)
